verses.text:
"Arrayed in fair linen, clean and white; for the fine linen is the righteousness of saints." - Rev. 19:8.
We shall walk with him in white; In that country pure and bright, Where the saints from earth's dark night may dwell;
And our robes shall be as snow, By the fountains of de-light, When the Lamb his ransomed ones shall lead.

We are washed in the blood of the Lamb, And our garments are white as the snow;
Where the day-break never closes, For the blessed light that shines Is the glo-ry of the Saviour's smile;
Robed in garments full and sweet, For ref-ting-ship complete, Washed, and in the Lamb's e-ter-nal smile.
